<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: and a few more....</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Azeraab">Azeraab</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:10 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: and a few more....<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=787" TARGET=_self>and a few more....</A> (Plug-TP)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> 1) Most people who play on the PvP server are not going to be

<BR>&gt; looking to kill monsters and take many many hours to arrive at a
<BR>&gt; decent character to play with in PvP situations. I would like to
<BR>&gt; see monsters give many more times the amount of experience than
<BR>&gt; they currently give. A level should take 30 minutes to an hour
<BR>&gt; max to obtain at any point. Although I am not 100% on what
<BR>&gt; increase of exp mobs should give on the PvP server...the current
<BR>&gt; system is way too slow.
<P>Ten times as much. It may seem like a lot, but unless they find a way to make low levels more survivable it's necessary. And hell it'll still take hours of boring mindless monster farming to get a single level.
<P>&gt; 2) Experience points lost on pvp combat. I dont know if this has
<BR>&gt; been covered yet but I will throw it in. This is a pvp server..I
<BR>&gt; am a large proponent of zero loss. Why? Few reasons. One, I wish
<BR>&gt; to be engaged in pvp combat..not running around trying to kill
<BR>&gt; mobs because I died and lost a level. Two, of course you lose
<BR>&gt; connect and die. The whole point of a PvP server is to be
<BR>&gt; fighting players...not killing mobs.
<P>I totally disagree. Death needs to be hard no matter what. I think if you gained xp for winning in PvP it would help mitigate the need for endless monster farming and still keep death scary.
<P>&gt; 4) Transportation. Again this is a PvP server dedicated to
<BR>&gt; player combat. UO used moongates to travel across britania.
<BR>&gt; Something similar should be used on the Equest PvP server. Dying
<BR>&gt; and having to travel an hour to get back to your friends is not
<BR>&gt; what I consider fun.
<P>After playing for a while as a variety of classes the only one that holds any appeal to me at all is druid, simply because they can teleport.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
